t=25>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=10>Root thread</a><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97970901514330>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Guide to grouping</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jan 17th 5:25 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>All of this stuff is really good, the main point is rangers don't have obviously powerful stuff.&nbsp;&nbsp;What we do have are flexible abilities which are only as useful as you can make them.  I seem to end up playing the tank more often than not, and I have learned one very important lesson from this, root rocks!  Sure warriors and pally's can taunt and take the dmg, but what happens when that orc would rather beat on your caster instead of the tank?  Root him, inform the group that he is rooted and let the caster back off.  That gives the group anywhere from 4-10 secs to deal with the problem, which in a good group is more than enough time.  I was in highpass the other evening and for quite some time was the primary healer and secondary tank for the group.  We spent some four hours where no one was ever above half hitpoints or mana, I was never able to buff anyone (all mana was going for heals and roots), but nobody died and we were not driven like sheep to the zone, ever.  You can be a great group player as a ranger if you use your skills the max, educate your party on what you can and cannot do, and keep them informed of what you are doing.  You can't tank like a war, pally, or even sk, but you can use taunt to spread out the dmg so your prim tanks aren't totally wiped out and you can use your weak ass heals to keep the main healers from wasting mana between battles when they should be medding.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>1 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97973317120797>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=10&mid=97973317120797>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=10&mid=97973317120797>RE: Guide to grouping</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=10&mid=97973317120797#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jan 17th 12:08 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have to second something mentioned in this post... Tell your party what youre capable of doing.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Heres what I learned in HighPass, fighting from level 15-19.  Plan your attacks with your group, keeping in mind that each group is different, and requires different tactics.  Rangers can fit into any group, as we do have a wide variety of skills.  Figure these skills out, and use them accordingly.  Also, know what other classes are capable of, and when planning your tactics out, think of these things.  Rogue in the group?  Let them know that youll try and fight opposite them, giving them a better chance to backstab.  Warrior in the group?  Offer to taunt-pong with them, and to /assist them at their request.  <br><br>Taunting:  If youre the main tank, taunt.  If youre secondary, taunt only when the main tank is low, or if a MOB is on a caster.<br><br>Casting:  You have spells, so use em.  Are they weak?  Yes.  Do 10 Burst of Flame casts add up?  Yes.  If a MOB is not on me, I attack, kick, and cast, dropping to about 1/3 total mana before saving it for emergency casting.  Snare and root effectively, too (someone mentioned rooting a MOB thats aggro'd on a caster... perfect).  Also, keep in mind that Lightning spells are AOE, so if you have 3 orcs bunched up on your group, its going to damage all of them.  Sure, we're not "nuking" things for 500+ points, but you'll find the DD spells add up over the course of a battle.  Also, be ready to heal and snare/root at a moments notice.  Save your group once with root, and they'll remember.  One final thing on casting, remember that your group has meditating downtime... use it.  My med was maxed as soon as I hit level 14, and its been that way since.  <br><br>Weapon Choices:  Max atleast two melee disciplines out.  I made this mistake, and had to backtrack to practise 2H slashing at level 16.  It took time, and no one likes seeing you hit for 1 point of damage consistently.  Also, use your weapons effectively... At level 19 for duel wielding, I used a Short Sword of Morin and a Polished Granite Tomahawk... When the PGT proc'd, I taunted no matter what, because I knew I had a buffer of "no damage taken" time.  Groups appreciate that kind of 'heads up' play.<br><br>Hotkeys:  Program them for spells, taunt, and in-battle communications.  I programmed one for "&lt;grouptalk&gt; incoming &lt;target&gt;", so when I track-pull, I announce what Ive got coming in.  I programmed one that lets the tank know Im assisting them with whatever the target is ("&lt;grouptalk&gt; assisting you with &lt;target&gt;").  <br><br>Attitude:  Rangers get a bad rap, and I dont agree with it.  That being said, having a bad attitude, or not playing to your full potential as a Ranger, isnt going to help you get into groups later.  I think Rangers alot of fun to play, and to play with, when you use the wide variety of skills you have.  <br><br>Good luck!!<br><br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
