	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I whole-heartedly agree that every group is different and requires different tactics.&nbsp;&nbsp;If a Ranger truly uses their skills wisely, they can fill MANY gaps.<br>   Need a healer?  &lt;Invite&gt; me.<br>   Need a tank?  &lt;Invite&gt; me.<br>   Need a good puller who can find the *best* spawns?  &lt;Invite&gt; me.<br><br>One note on taunt, I disagree with the original poster.  There are 3 situations where taunt can be the key to being welcomed back into groups:<br>1&gt; If you ARE the main tank<br>2&gt; If the main tanks are incapable of keeping the MOBs off casters (happens a lot - there are a lot of warriors out there that don't have &lt;taunt&gt; hot-keyed because "I wanted to use that button for ... skill instead").<br>3&gt; You are grouped with rogues.  Rogues love me because I can almost guarantee that I can keep the MOB on me.  "Oh, you backstabbed for 75 points!  Twice?  Cool."  The extra damage I take is minimized by the MOB's quick death.<br><br>I know of 1 wizard, 1 cleric, and 2 rogues that invite me into their groups just because I know how and when to &lt;taunt&gt; (and they don't invite their previous tanks back...wonder why...).<br><br>~~Stonewater</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
